    slug: "next-gen-cms-now-available-for-webflow-enterprise",
    title: "Next-Gen CMS: Now Available for Webflow Enterprise",
    excerpt: "Webflow Enterprise sites now run on a modern CMS architecture, unlocking higher content scale, richer data models, and increased design flexibility.",
    content: "<p>The next generation of Webflow's CMS has officially launched for Enterprise customers, bringing a complete architectural overhaul that fundamentally changes how teams manage content at scale.</p><h2>What's New</h2><p>The new CMS architecture introduces several groundbreaking improvements. Content collections can now handle significantly more items — up to 100,000 per collection, compared to the previous 10,000 limit. This is a game-changer for large organizations managing extensive product catalogs, resource libraries, or content-heavy publications.</p><p>Richer data models mean you can now create more complex content structures with nested references, multi-reference fields, and custom field types that better reflect your real-world data relationships.</p><h2>Why It Matters for Template Creators</h2><p>For Flowbites creators building Webflow templates, this means you can design templates that leverage these new CMS capabilities. Templates with advanced filtering, dynamic content relationships, and large-scale content management are now possible — and in high demand from enterprise buyers.</p><p>Consider updating your existing Webflow templates to take advantage of the new CMS features. Templates that demonstrate enterprise-grade CMS usage will stand out in the marketplace and command premium pricing.</p><h2>Getting Started</h2><p>If you're building Webflow templates for the enterprise market, start exploring the new CMS API and data model capabilities. The migration is automatic for existing Enterprise sites, so your templates will work seamlessly with the new architecture.</p>",
