    slug: "webflow-agency-website-templates-winning-new-clients",
    title: "Webflow Agency Website Templates: Winning New Clients",
    excerpt: "Design agency website templates that showcase work, demonstrate expertise, and convert visitors into clients.",
    content: "<p>Agencies need websites that practice what they preach. An agency's website IS their portfolio — if it doesn't look amazing, why would a client trust them to build their website? Agency templates need to be the best of the best.</p><h2>Case Study Showcase</h2><p>Design a CMS-driven case study system with: project overview, challenge/solution narrative, results metrics, client testimonial, and full-screen imagery. Allow agencies to tag case studies by industry, service type, and technology. The case study template should be flexible enough to accommodate different project types.</p><h2>Service Pages</h2><p>Create individual service page templates: web design, development, branding, SEO, content strategy. Each service page should include: service description, process/methodology, pricing tiers (optional), related case studies, and a CTA to book a consultation.</p><h2>Team and Culture</h2><p>Agencies sell people as much as services. Design team member profiles with: photos, bios, specialties, social links, and featured work. Include a culture page with behind-the-scenes photos, values statements, and a careers section with CMS-driven job listings.</p><p>Agency templates sell consistently on Flowbites because agencies are always looking for inspiration and time-saving starting points. Your template becomes part of their toolkit.</p>",
    category: "Webflow",
