    title: "Wix vs Squarespace: Which Platform Is Better in 2026",
    excerpt: "A detailed comparison of Wix and Squarespace in 2026, covering design, features, pricing, and which platform suits different needs.",
    content: "<p>Wix and Squarespace are the two most recognized website builders for small businesses and entrepreneurs, and in 2026 both platforms have evolved considerably. Choosing between them depends on your specific priorities: design control, built-in features, pricing, ease of use, and ecosystem extensibility. This comparison cuts through marketing claims to give you an honest assessment of where each platform excels and where it falls short. Whether you are building for yourself or selecting a platform for a client, understanding these differences helps you make a decision that you will not regret six months later.</p><h2>Design and Customization</h2><p><strong>Squarespace</strong> is known for its curated, opinionated design aesthetic. Templates are beautiful out of the box, with carefully chosen typography, spacing, and color palettes. The trade-off is less customization freedom; you work within the template's design system rather than building from scratch. Squarespace 7.1 improved flexibility with sections and layout blocks, but you still cannot achieve the same level of custom design as other platforms. <strong>Wix</strong>, particularly through Wix Studio, offers significantly more design freedom. You can position elements with precision, apply custom CSS, use advanced grid layouts, and modify virtually every visual property. For designers who want full creative control, Wix provides more room to express a unique vision. For business owners who want a polished site with minimal design decisions, Squarespace's guided approach is faster.</p><h2>Features and Ecosystem</h2><p>Wix has a clear advantage in built-in business features. Its app market offers hundreds of native and third-party applications for e-commerce, bookings, restaurants, events, fitness, and more. Wix Stores, Wix Bookings, and Wix Blog are mature, full-featured solutions that compete with dedicated SaaS tools. Squarespace offers solid built-in e-commerce and scheduling features, but its extension ecosystem is more limited. For content-focused sites like portfolios and blogs, Squarespace's native tools are elegant and sufficient. For businesses that need specialized functionality like appointment booking, membership areas, or multi-vendor marketplaces, Wix's app ecosystem provides more options without requiring external service subscriptions.</p><p>Pricing is broadly comparable between the two platforms, though Wix offers a free tier with Wix branding that Squarespace does not match. Both platforms charge for premium features like custom domains, e-commerce, and advanced analytics. Performance has improved on both platforms, with Wix closing the gap on page speed that historically favored Squarespace. SEO capabilities are similar, with both offering meta tag controls, sitemaps, and structured data. For template creators on Flowbites, the Wix market is larger due to the platform's wider adoption and more diverse user base. Consider building templates for both platforms if your workflow supports it, as this doubles your addressable market with relatively modest additional effort.</p>",
